This MIT license covers the ononceditor wrapper code only.

The bundled editor runtime under `editor-runtime/` is the KEDITOR distribution
(a TinyMCE 4.x fork), licensed under the GNU LGPL v2.1. Its license text ships at
`editor-runtime/LICENSE`; the corresponding upstream source is the official
release at https://t1.daumcdn.net/keditor/opensource/KEDITOR-0.7.21.zip and
https://github.com/tinymce/tinymce .

The bundled KEDITOR runtime has been MODIFIED from the upstream 0.7.21 release
(2026): unused plugins removed, toolbar/menu icons re-skinned, the link (klink)
plugin patched, and stylesheets adjusted. All such changes are confined to the
files under `editor-runtime/`.

The code-block feature bundles CodeMirror (MIT), and the runtime bundles the
core-js and regenerator-runtime polyfills (MIT). Syntax highlighting
(highlight.js, BSD-3-Clause) and the Pretendard font are loaded at runtime from a
CDN (jsDelivr) rather than bundled. Third-party license texts ship at
`editor-runtime/THIRD-PARTY-LICENSES.txt`.
